id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts0
label: ESFJc
text: Throughout my entire life I could count my close friends on one hand.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts1
label: ESFJc
text: In fact, I don't think that number has ever reached three.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts2
label: ESFJc
text: A lot of people have the wrong idea about

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts3
label: ESFJc
text: introverts and I say that because for a very long time I had the wrong idea about introverts and so I

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts4
label: ESFJc
text: just want to share my perspective.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts5
label: ESFJc
text: It's really easy to look up the word introvert and see that the definition is someone who is shy or quiet.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts6
label: ESFJc
text: Obviously, I'm not going to say that that's flat-out wrong.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts7
label: ESFJc
text: It's in the dictionary after all, but unfortunately, I feel like things are not so black and white.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts8
label: ESFJc
text: I know it sounds crazy

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts9
label: ESFJc
text: but I didn't realize how introverted I am until very recently. And I think this is an

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts10
label: ESFJc
text: unbelievably valuable thing to know about yourself whether you're introverted or not. I'm just gonna speak for myself here.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts11
label: ESFJc
text: Understanding who I am and, more crucially, how I operate has been a very confusing but important process for me.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts12
label: ESFJc
text: I feel like as I figure these things out little by little I've been able to make better decisions

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts13
label: ESFJc
text: for myself and where I want to put my time. At my age, it feels like there's a lot of social pressure

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts14
label: ESFJc
text: to be a partying and sexually active like 21 year old, you know.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts15
label: ESFJc
text: I think of movies like American Pie. And it's so backwards because even just a couple generations ago things were so different.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts16
label: ESFJc
text: Now, however, that seems kind of like the image of happiness that we all see on social media and also mainstream media.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts17
label: ESFJc
text: I explored this a lot during my 30 days without alcohol.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts18
label: ESFJc
text: And that's a separate video

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts19
label: ESFJc
text: But I think the point of why I'm bringing this up is because I think there are other ways

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts20
label: ESFJc
text: to squeeze the juice out of life in your twenties.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts21
label: ESFJc
text: And I know that me saying I'm an introvert is going to surprise some of you guys because like I'm not socially awkward.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts22
label: ESFJc
text: I don't have a problem speaking to the camera.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts23
label: ESFJc
text: Speaking in front of people. Speaking with people. I can be really loud.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts24
label: ESFJc
text: I mean I love connecting with people.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts25
label: ESFJc
text: That's the whole reason why I'm doing this, you know human interactions fascinate me

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts26
label: ESFJc
text: but above all I think that the most

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts27
label: ESFJc
text: important relationship that you have in life is with yourself. For me, everything fits into three categories.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts28
label: ESFJc
text: Very close deep relationships. These kinds of relationships feed me, and my creativity.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts29
label: ESFJc
text: Finding people that I can connect with on or even close to this level is really difficult though and doesn't happen very often.

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts30
label: ESFJc

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts31
label: ESFJc
text: Superficial relationships

label: ESFJc

id: ESFJc_A Video For Introverts33
label: ESFJc
text: These kinds of relationships and interactions. Don't just drain me, um

label: ESFJc

label: ESFJc

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -0
label: ESTJc
text: Authenticity is a word that you hear

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -1
label: ESTJc
text: flying around self help circles and

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -2
label: ESTJc
text: psychology offices and

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -3
label: ESTJc
text: spiritual communities all the time.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -4
label: ESTJc
text:
I myself am leading an 
authenticity movement

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -5
label: ESTJc
text: But what the hell does that mean?

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -6
label: ESTJc
text: In this episode I'm going to tell you

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -7
label: ESTJc
text: "How To Be Authentic"

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -8
label: ESTJc
text: Something that is authentic is not copied.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -9
label: ESTJc
text: It's genuine, it's real and it's true.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -10
label: ESTJc
text: As authenticity applies to a human beings

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -11
label: ESTJc
text: we must follow the reality that each

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -12
label: ESTJc
text: and every person comes into this life as a

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -13
label: ESTJc
text: unique expression of source consciousness.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -14
label: ESTJc
text: This means, each person comes with

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -15
label: ESTJc
text:
a unique essence, like
an energetic signature

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -16
label: ESTJc
text:
and our unique purpose 
and unique thoughts

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -17
label: ESTJc
text:
and unique feelings 
and unique desires

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -18
label: ESTJc
text:
and unique needs 
and unique role within

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -19
label: ESTJc
text:
the greater universe is 
embedded in that essence.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -20
label: ESTJc
text: Our process of progression through this

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -21
label: ESTJc
text:
planet should be a 
process of unfolding.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -22
label: ESTJc
text: Kind of like when a flower blooms.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -23
label: ESTJc
text: So you can recognize each person

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -24
label: ESTJc
text: as if they are a lotus blossom.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -25
label: ESTJc
text:
Their unique essence 
which is encoded with

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -26
label: ESTJc
text:
their purpose and 
everything else that we

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -27
label: ESTJc
text: think has to do with authenticity

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -28
label: ESTJc
text: is like a pearl inside of that lotus.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -29
label: ESTJc
text: Now... if we are allowed to unfold

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -30
label: ESTJc
text: it naturally opens, exposing that pearl

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -31
label: ESTJc
text: but the process of socialization

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -32
label: ESTJc
text: on planet earth does not go this way.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -33
label: ESTJc
text: If we allowed an unfolding

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -34
label: ESTJc
text: of the authentic aspect of each person

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -35
label: ESTJc
text: the parenting and socialization process

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -36
label: ESTJc
text:
would be a process of 
enabling a child to unfold.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -37
label: ESTJc
text:
If we did not interfere 
with this process

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -38
label: ESTJc
text: and simply met the unique needs

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -39
label: ESTJc
text: of the unique child in front of us,

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -40
label: ESTJc
text: it would naturally happen this way.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -41
label: ESTJc
text:
But we live in a world 
where the process

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -42
label: ESTJc
text: of socialization and therefore parenting,

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -43
label: ESTJc
text:
is quite often an impediment
to the process of unfolding.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -44
label: ESTJc
text: When we come into the world

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -45
label: ESTJc
text: people do not look at us as if

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -46
label: ESTJc
text: we are a lotus blossom

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -47
label: ESTJc
text: and like it's their job to help us unfold

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -48
label: ESTJc
text: so they can see the mystery and the magic

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -49
label: ESTJc
text:
and the present in the 
gift of what we are.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -50
label: ESTJc
text: Instead they look at us like we are

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -51
label: ESTJc
text: raw material that needs to be molded

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -52
label: ESTJc
text: Almost like we do not have

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -53
label: ESTJc
text: an innate essence and they know what's

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -54
label: ESTJc
text:
best for that person to become
so let's shape them into that.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -55
label: ESTJc
text: They tell us that certain things are

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -56
label: ESTJc
text: acceptable and if we are those things,

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -57
label: ESTJc
text: we will be good and be safe.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -58
label: ESTJc
text: And other things are unacceptable and

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -59
label: ESTJc
text: if we do that, we will be bad and unsafe

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -60
label: ESTJc
text: So naturally all of these vulnerable

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -61
label: ESTJc
text: aspects of us, anything that might be

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -62
label: ESTJc
text: real about us, that might be unacceptable

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -63
label: ESTJc
text: have to be hidden from view.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -64
label: ESTJc
text: We begin a process of splitting ourselves.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -65
label: ESTJc
text: We put forward only the things about us

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -66
label: ESTJc
text: that make us loved and safe in the world

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -67
label: ESTJc
text: and the rest we keep hidden.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -68
label: ESTJc
text:
It is as if we will not 
let certain lotus

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -69
label: ESTJc
text:
petals open and 
therefore keep the

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -70
label: ESTJc
text:
pearl hidden so as 
to fit into the world,

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -71
label: ESTJc
text: be loved and feel safe.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -72
label: ESTJc
text:
What this means that 
our personalities are

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -73
label: ESTJc
text: in essence, totally fake.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -74
label: ESTJc
text:
Because the parts 
of you that you put

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -75
label: ESTJc
text:
forward to the world 
(your personality) -

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -76
label: ESTJc
text:
those are just the 
things that kept you

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -77
label: ESTJc
text:
the most safe and most 
accepted in the world.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -78
label: ESTJc
text:
And that changes 
based on whatever

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -79
label: ESTJc
text: external condition, culture,

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -80
label: ESTJc
text: fill in the blank, you grew up in.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -81
label: ESTJc
text:
Our personalities are merely the 
part of us that we identified with

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -82
label: ESTJc
text:
or developed so as to 
stay safe and away from

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -83
label: ESTJc
text:
vulnerability in the 
specific situations

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -84
label: ESTJc
text: that we were raised in.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -85
label: ESTJc
text:
We suppress, reject, 
deny and disown

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -86
label: ESTJc
text:
the aspects that make us vulnerable
or get us disapproved of in the world.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -87
label: ESTJc
text: By doing this, they become subconscious.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -88
label: ESTJc
text: They are buried outside of our awareness

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -89
label: ESTJc
text: and we do not know they even exist.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -90
label: ESTJc
text: To understand more about this process,

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -91
label: ESTJc
text: I encourage you to watch my video titled:

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -92
label: ESTJc
text: "Fragmentation, The Worldwide Disease"

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -93
label: ESTJc
text: We can only be authentic to the degree

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -94
label: ESTJc
text: that we currently know ourselves.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -95
label: ESTJc
text: That's scary, it means we

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -96
label: ESTJc
text: can only be authentic to the

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -97
label: ESTJc
text: degree that we are self aware.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -98
label: ESTJc
text: That's scary, because the majority of us

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -99
label: ESTJc
text: is suppressed into our subconscious

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -100
label: ESTJc
text: Long story short guys -

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -101
label: ESTJc
text: we are not very aware of ourselves.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -102
label: ESTJc
text: Most of us are basically copies.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -103
label: ESTJc
text: Copies of what we saw succeeding

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -104
label: ESTJc
text: in other people.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -105
label: ESTJc
text: We are not genuine, not real and

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -106
label: ESTJc
text: do not reflect what is true at our core.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -107
label: ESTJc
text: Our commitment to unfolding usually

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -108
label: ESTJc
text: ends up being something that we have

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -109
label: ESTJc
text: to take charge of and allow to

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -110
label: ESTJc
text: happen in spite of the world.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -111
label: ESTJc
text: We end up having to sort through

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -112
label: ESTJc
text: illusion to find what is real about us.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -113
label: ESTJc
text: The process of becoming authentic,

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -114
label: ESTJc
text:
which is finding your essence again 
and following that and allowing it to

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -115
label: ESTJc
text:
be shared with the world is no 
different that the process of awakening.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -116
label: ESTJc
text:
And so, for the sake of awakening, 
I will give you some tips about

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -117
label: ESTJc
text: how to be authentic.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -118
label: ESTJc
text:
Step 1 .The simplest 
way to understand

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -119
label: ESTJc
text:
authenticity (aside from discovering 
your innate essence)

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -120
label: ESTJc
text:
is it's the conscious mending of
the incongruences between your

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -121
label: ESTJc
text: inner world and your outer world.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -122
label: ESTJc
text: That means, whats on the inside is

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -123
label: ESTJc
text:
exactly the same as 
what's on the outside.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -124
label: ESTJc
text: This is the opposite of

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -125
label: ESTJc
text: the wolf in sheep's clothing.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -126
label: ESTJc
text:
I know that many of 
you have heard that.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -127
label: ESTJc
text: So obviously, if there is a sheep that's

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -128
label: ESTJc
text: in wolf's clothing, or a wolf that's

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -129
label: ESTJc
text: in sheep's clothing, either way,

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -130
label: ESTJc
text: it's not authentic, because

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -131
label: ESTJc
text: what's on the inside is not a direct

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -132
label: ESTJc
text: reflection of what's on the outside.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -133
label: ESTJc
text: There are all kinds of inconguences

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -134
label: ESTJc
text: in the world when it comes to people.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -135
label: ESTJc
text: For example, let's take a guy who

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -136
label: ESTJc
text: hates his work.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -137
label: ESTJc
text: On the inside he really wants

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -138
label: ESTJc
text:
to do something else, 
so you could say

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -139
label: ESTJc
text: that his external job does not match

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -140
label: ESTJc
text: his internal desires for what job

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -141
label: ESTJc
text: he wants to have.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -142
label: ESTJc
text: That's inauthentic.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -143
label: ESTJc
text:
When a person says 
they like someone or

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -144
label: ESTJc
text:
acts as if they do, 
when the truth is they

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -145
label: ESTJc
text:
hate them and want 
to be nowhere near

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -146
label: ESTJc
text: them, this is inauthentic.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -147
label: ESTJc
text:
When a person says 
they are not artistic,

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -148
label: ESTJc
text:
because they suppressed that
inside themselves long ago,

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -149
label: ESTJc
text: this is not authentic.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -150
label: ESTJc
text:
When a person denied 
how they feel

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -151
label: ESTJc
text:
because they have 
learned certain feelings

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -152
label: ESTJc
text:
are not acceptable, 
this is not authentic.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -153
label: ESTJc
text:
When we care so 
much about seeing

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -154
label: ESTJc
text:
ourselves as good that 
we cannot admit to

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -155
label: ESTJc
text:
aspects within us 
that wouldnt seem

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -156
label: ESTJc
text: so good, we are inauthentic.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -157
label: ESTJc
text:
When we have two 
Facebook accounts,

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -158
label: ESTJc
text:
one for the people 
we know from work

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -159
label: ESTJc
text:
and family and one 
for the things we are

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -160
label: ESTJc
text:
actually interested 
in that they would

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -161
label: ESTJc
text: negatively judge us for,

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -162
label: ESTJc
text: we are inauthentic.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -163
label: ESTJc
text:
When we are gay 
but we pretend to

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -164
label: ESTJc
text:
be straight, we are 
being inauthentic.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -165
label: ESTJc
text: To be honest, our entire society

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -166
label: ESTJc
text: is based on pretenses.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -167
label: ESTJc
text:
But the time has 
come for this to end,

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -168
label: ESTJc
text:
it is one of the greatest 
barriers to awakening.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -169
label: ESTJc
text: So the question to live by is:

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -170
label: ESTJc
text:
Is there any incongruence between 
my outer self and inner self?

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -171
label: ESTJc
text: 2. It is a far bigger deal to not even

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -172
label: ESTJc
text:
admit to or not even 
realize, even worse,

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -173
label: ESTJc
text:
that there is an 
incongruency between

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -174
label: ESTJc
text: your outer and inner world

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -175
label: ESTJc
text: then it is to just deliberately choose

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -176
label: ESTJc
text: to be inauthentic.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -177
label: ESTJc
text: I would love if we lived in a world

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -178
label: ESTJc
text:
where 24 hours a day 
every person could

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -179
label: ESTJc
text: be authentic, but let's just be honest -

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -180
label: ESTJc
text:
one of us can take that 
amount of honesty.

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -181
label: ESTJc
text: And on top of that,

id: ESTJc_How To Be Authentic - Teal Swan -182
label: ESTJc
text:

label: ISTP
text: So it never gets old.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan43
label: ISTP
text: It never gets boring.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan44
label: ISTP
text: I think that's fun.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan45
label: ISTP
text:
So it's exciting
because it's dynamic.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan46
label: ISTP
text: Every transaction is different.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan47
label: ISTP
text: That's atypical for jobs.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan48
label: ISTP
text:
Typically, a job becomes
somewhat routine over time

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan49
label: ISTP
text: and can become somewhat boring.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan50
label: ISTP
text:
Not true on deals because
every deal is so different.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan51
label: ISTP
text:
Third reason I
think it's exciting

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan52
label: ISTP
text: is because it's intense.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan53
label: ISTP
text:
You are going to
spend a lot of time

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan54
label: ISTP
text:
and a lot of energy
working on transactions,

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan55
label: ISTP
text:
if you become an investment
banker or a corporate lawyer.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan56
label: ISTP
text:
You're going to be sequestered
in conference rooms

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan57
label: ISTP
text: with your clients.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan58
label: ISTP
text:
And you're going to get
to know them very well.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan59
label: ISTP
text:
And you're going
to work very hard.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan60
label: ISTP
text: And that's not always fun.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan61
label: ISTP
text: But it's mostly fun, I think.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan62
label: ISTP
text:
And in hindsight, when
you look back on it,

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan63
label: ISTP
text: you'll appreciate that it's fun.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan64
label: ISTP
text:
But it's exciting
because it's so intense.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan65
label: ISTP
text:
So I think the job is exciting
because it's important.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan66
label: ISTP
text:
What you're working
on is important.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan67
label: ISTP
text: And you can make a difference.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan68
label: ISTP
text: Because it's dynamic.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan69
label: ISTP
text:
It changes from deal to
deal and even within a deal.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan70
label: ISTP
text: And because it's very intense.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan71
label: ISTP
text:
So what skills do I think are
necessary to do the job well?

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan72
label: ISTP
text:
I think there are
six tangible skills

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan73
label: ISTP
text:
that I believe are
necessary, and then four

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan74
label: ISTP
text: intangible skills.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan75
label: ISTP
text:
The six tangible skills start
with interpersonal skills.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan76
label: ISTP
text:
You need to have strong
interpersonal skills.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan77
label: ISTP
text:
Now, I don't mean that in
the sense that some of you

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan78
label: ISTP
text:
may think in this room or people
outside of this room may think.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan79
label: ISTP
text:
I don't mean
interpersonal skills

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan80
label: ISTP
text:
in the sense of sort of slap
you on the back salesman

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan81
label: ISTP
text: or saleswoman types of skills.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan82
label: ISTP
text: I don't mean schmoozing skills.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan83
label: ISTP
text:
I mean the ability to
convey to the client

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan84
label: ISTP
text:
that they should have confidence
in you, that you are competent.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan85
label: ISTP
text:
And that they should
have confidence in you.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan86
label: ISTP
text: Secondly, quantitative skills.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan87
label: ISTP
text:
Quantitative skills
are important if you're

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan88
label: ISTP
text: going to work on transactions.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan89
label: ISTP
text:
Now, you do not need to have
been a math major or a physics

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan90
label: ISTP
text:
major or an engineer
in college to have

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan91
label: ISTP
text:
the prerequisite
quantitative skills.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan92
label: ISTP
text:
But you need to be
facile with numbers.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan93
label: ISTP
text:
You need to be
comfortable with numbers.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan94
label: ISTP
text:
Because much of what you
do as a transaction lawyer

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan95
label: ISTP
text:
and definitely as an
investment banker will involve

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan96
label: ISTP
text: numbers and numerical analysis.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan97
label: ISTP
text:
So you need to be comfortable
working with numbers.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan98
label: ISTP
text:
Thirdly, you have to have
an interest in business.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan99
label: ISTP
text:
You do not, contrary
to popular belief,

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan100
label: ISTP
text:
need to have a
business background.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan101
label: ISTP
text:
You do not need to have worked
in business for four, five,

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan102
label: ISTP
text: or three, or two, or one year.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan103
label: ISTP
text:
But you should have an
interest in business.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan104
label: ISTP
text:
And the way I would say you
could manifest that interest

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan105
label: ISTP
text:
now, or what you might
want to be doing now

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan106
label: ISTP
text:
at this stage of
your careers, is just

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan107
label: ISTP
text:
The Wall Street Journal
a couple of times a week,

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan108
label: ISTP
text:
not even everyday, just
a couple of times a week,

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan109
label: ISTP
text:
just the front page,
just the front page.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan110
label: ISTP
text:
So take 10 minutes,
that's all it

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan111
label: ISTP
text:
takes to read the front page
of The Wall Street Journal

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan112
label: ISTP
text: two or three days a week.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan113
label: ISTP
text:
And you'll become familiar with
what's going on economically

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan114
label: ISTP
text:
around the world
and what's going

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan115
label: ISTP
text:
on among some of the leading
companies around the world.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan116
label: ISTP
text:
So develop an interest,
acquire an interest,

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan117
label: ISTP
text: fake an interest in business.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan118
label: ISTP
text:
But you know, have an interest,
at least, in business.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan119
label: ISTP
text:
Fourthly, you need
to be discreet.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan120
label: ISTP
text:
You will be entrusted with
confidential information that's

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan121
label: ISTP
text: very, very valuable.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan122
label: ISTP
text:
And you don't want to
be the person who's

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan123
label: ISTP
text:
talking about the transaction
upon which they are working

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan124
label: ISTP
text:
when they're on a train,
or in an elevator,

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan125
label: ISTP
text: or at a restaurant.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan126
label: ISTP
text:
You do not want to be divulging
this confidential information.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan127
label: ISTP
text: You need to be discreet.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan128
label: ISTP
text:
You need to treat
it with discretion.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan129
label: ISTP
text:
And you need to
exercise good judgment.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan130
label: ISTP
text:
Next, you need to be
OK with confrontation.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan131
label: ISTP
text:
A popular misconception that
some people in law school

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan132
label: ISTP
text:
have is they think of litigators
as sort of conflict seekers.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan133
label: ISTP
text:
And they think of transactional
lawyers, or corporate lawyers,

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan134
label: ISTP
text:
as the people who want
to avoid conflict.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan135
label: ISTP
text:
You do not get to avoid conflict
by becoming a corporate lawyer

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan136
label: ISTP
text: or an investment banker.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan137
label: ISTP
text:
You're going to work
on a transaction.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan138
label: ISTP
text:
The people sitting on the other
side of the table from you

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan139
label: ISTP
text:
have adverse interests
to those of your client.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan140
label: ISTP
text:
And you're going to have to
conflict with that person.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan141
label: ISTP
text:
You're going to have to
negotiate against that person.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan142
label: ISTP
text:
And you're going
to have conflict.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan143
label: ISTP
text: So you have to be OK with that.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan144
label: ISTP
text: You have to be OK with conflict.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan145
label: ISTP
text:
Last tangible skill
is you need to be

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan146
label: ISTP
text: able to put the client first.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan147
label: ISTP
text: A lot of people say that.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan148
label: ISTP
text: What does that really mean?

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan149
label: ISTP
text:
It means that you need to
be there for the client

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan150
label: ISTP
text: whenever they need you.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan151
label: ISTP
text:
You need to respond to
their emails immediately.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan152
label: ISTP
text:
You need to call them back
immediately when they call you.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan153
label: ISTP
text:
One, you want to really be
responsive to the client.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan154
label: ISTP
text:
But two, you want to
just as importantly,

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan155
label: ISTP
text:
convey to the client
that they are a priority.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan156
label: ISTP
text:
So you're going to get calls at
2:00, 3:00 4:00 in the morning.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan157
label: ISTP
text:
You got to return emails 2:00,
3:00, 4:00 in the morning.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan158
label: ISTP
text:
You got to return
them really fast.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan159
label: ISTP
text:
You're going to spend
all-nighters with the client.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan160
label: ISTP
text: You're going to work very hard.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan161
label: ISTP
text:
You want to do, on
top of that, whatever

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan162
label: ISTP
text:
you can to make the client
feel comfortable that they

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan163
label: ISTP
text: are a priority for you.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan164
label: ISTP
text:
So those are the
six tangible skills

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan165
label: ISTP
text:
that I would say are
necessary to do deals

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan166
label: ISTP
text:
or to work on
corporate transactions.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan167
label: ISTP
text:
Four intangible
skills, the first

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan168
label: ISTP
text:
is it's helpful to be an
open book, or a blank sheet

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan169
label: ISTP
text:
of paper, whatever analogy you
want to use to convey what I'm

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan170
label: ISTP
text:
trying to convey, which is that
you want to be a student when

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan171
label: ISTP
text:
you first start
out on this career

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan172
label: ISTP
text:
as a transactional lawyer
or an investment banker.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan173
label: ISTP
text:
You want to find somebody who
does this job really well.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan174
label: ISTP
text:
And you want to
study that person.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan175
label: ISTP
text:
Put your ego aside and
learn as much as you can

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan176
label: ISTP
text: from that person.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan177
label: ISTP
text:
You need to be a
student of the business

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan178
label: ISTP
text: for the first couple of years.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan179
label: ISTP
text:
I can't tell you how many
people make this mistake.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan180
label: ISTP
text:
They come in with
preconceived notions

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan181
label: ISTP
text:
of what will make them
good or bad at doing deals.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan182
label: ISTP
text: And they're usually wrong.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan183
label: ISTP
text: And you can't do that.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan184
label: ISTP
text:
You need to put aside
any preconceived notions

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan185
label: ISTP
text:
that you might have and be
willing to learn from people

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan186
label: ISTP
text:
who are really good at
doing what you're hopefully

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan187
label: ISTP
text: going to do.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan188
label: ISTP
text: So be a student.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan189
label: ISTP
text: That's very, very important.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan190
label: ISTP
text: Secondly, have a system.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan191
label: ISTP
text:
The best transactional
lawyers and investment bankers

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan192
label: ISTP
text:
have a system that they
use for covering clients

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan193
label: ISTP
text: for doing deals.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan194
label: ISTP
text:
And it involves everything
from mundane things

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan195
label: ISTP
text: to more sophisticated things.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan196
label: ISTP
text: They don't just wing it.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan197
label: ISTP
text:
They actually have a system that
they've put together over time.

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan198
label: ISTP
text:
And they follow that system
throughout the course

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan199
label: ISTP
text:
of the deal, from the time they
make the pitch to the client

id: ISTP_"Are You Destined to Deal?" With Goldman Sachs Managing Director Jim Donovan200
label: ISTP
text:
to try and convince them to hire
them to the time they attend

text: I'm exhausted.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!146
label: ESFJc
text: Cool?

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!147
label: ESFJc
text:
It means you want
to go to sleep now.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!148
label: ESFJc
text:
Or if you're exhausted of this conversation,
then no more, I can't do any more, I'm done,

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!149
label: ESFJc
text: it's over.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!150
label: ESFJc
text:
"Poor", a lot of people like
to use the word "poor".

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!151
label: ESFJc
text:
Most native speakers don't even use the word
I'm going to teach you because it's so strong.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!152
label: ESFJc
text:
If you say: "I'm very poor"
it means I have no money.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!153
label: ESFJc
text:
If I'm destitute, you live on the street,
my friend, you eat with the rats.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!154
label: ESFJc
text: Okay?

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!155
label: ESFJc
text:
You and the rats share Kentucky Fried
Chicken out of garbage at night.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!156
label: ESFJc
text: All right?

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!157
label: ESFJc
text: I'm just saying.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!158
label: ESFJc
text:
But if you say: "I'm destitute",
it means: "I'm very poor."

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!159
label: ESFJc
text:
You want to remember this word for the next
time your English friend says: -"Hey, Jimmy.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!160
label: ESFJc
text: Can I borrow 5 dollars?"

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!161
label: ESFJc
text: -"Sorry, dude.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!162
label: ESFJc
text: I'm destitute."

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!163
label: ESFJc
text:
He will give you 5 dollars and be
like: "I didn't know it was so bad.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!164
label: ESFJc
text:
You're so poor,
you're destitute?"

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!165
label: ESFJc
text: It means my house is...

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!166
label: ESFJc
text: I live on the street.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!167
label: ESFJc
text: My house, I have nothing.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!168
label: ESFJc
text: I'm destitute.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!169
label: ESFJc
text:
After the divorce, most
people are destitute.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!170
label: ESFJc
text: Don't get divorced.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!171
label: ESFJc
text: Okay, next.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!172
label: ESFJc
text: "Rich", "very rich".

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!173
label: ESFJc
text:
I know, students love to: "I'm studying English
because one day I hope to be very, very rich.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!174
label: ESFJc
text:
I'm telling you I'm
going to be rich.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!175
label: ESFJc
text: You know?

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!176
label: ESFJc
text: I'm going to be very rich."

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!177
label: ESFJc
text: And I go: "You want to be rich?

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!178
label: ESFJc
text: I want to be wealthy."

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!179
label: ESFJc
text:
And they say: "Teacher,
what's the difference?

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!180
label: ESFJc
text:
'Very rich' means I
have everything."

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!181
label: ESFJc
text:
So I say: "Okay, so, you
know Michael Jordan?"

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!182
label: ESFJc
text:
They go: "Yes, yes, he's a very rich
man", I go: -"Yeah, he's very rich."

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!183
label: ESFJc
text:
-"They pay him
millions of dollars."

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!184
label: ESFJc
text: I go: "Yeah, yeah, yeah."

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!185
label: ESFJc
text:
I say: "I want to be the man who pays
Michael Jordan -- that guy's wealthy."

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!186
label: ESFJc
text:
Sudden silence, and then their vocabulary
changes instantly: "I would like to be wealthy,

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!187
label: ESFJc
text:
yes, I think it would be
superb to be wealthy.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!188
label: ESFJc
text:
In fact, I'm looking for a rapid change in
my environment so I can become wealthy."

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!189
label: ESFJc
text: I go: "Oh, you understand."

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!190
label: ESFJc
text:
Change your vocabulary, change
your brain, change your life.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!191
label: ESFJc
text: Right?

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!192
label: ESFJc
text:
Okay, anyway, before I go on that, I don't
want to become dull going over the same points

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!193
label: ESFJc
text: again and again.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!194
label: ESFJc
text:
I'm going to try to
keep it brief, okay?

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!195
label: ESFJc
text:
Ah, I do want to talk about one
difference here, that's why I have it.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!196
label: ESFJc
text:
We talked about hot, "scalding" and
"scorching", they're not quite the same.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!197
label: ESFJc
text:
These both mean very hot, but usually we
use "scolding" for liquids, like water.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!198
label: ESFJc
text: Right?

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!199
label: ESFJc
text:
The water is scolding, it
will burn you it's so hot.

id: ESFJc_Improve your Vocabulary: Stop saying VERY!200
label: ESFJc
text:
And we say "scorching" for hot
for heat like the summer sun.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity0
label: ISTPc
text:
Translator: TED Translators admin
Reviewer: Allam Zedan

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity1
label: ISTPc
text:
The people in the back,
can you hear me clearly?

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity2
label: ISTPc
text: OK, good.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity3
label: ISTPc
text: Have you ever held a question in mind

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity4
label: ISTPc
text:
for so long that it becomes
part of how you think?

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity5
label: ISTPc
text:
Maybe even part of who you are
as a person?

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity6
label: ISTPc
text:
Well I've had a question in my mind 
for many, many years

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity7
label: ISTPc
text:
and that is: 
How can you speed up learning?

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity8
label: ISTPc
text: Now, this is an interesting question

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity9
label: ISTPc
text: because if you speed up learning,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity10
label: ISTPc
text: you can spend less time at school.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity11
label: ISTPc
text: And if you learn really fast,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity12
label: ISTPc
text:
you probably 
wouldn't have to go to school at all.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity13
label: ISTPc
text:
Now, when I was young, 
school was sort of OK but...

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity14
label: ISTPc
text:
I found quite often that school 
got in the way of learning

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity15
label: ISTPc
text:
so I had this question in mind: 
How do you learn faster?

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity16
label: ISTPc
text:
And this began when I was 
very, very young,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity17
label: ISTPc
text: when I was 11 years old,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity18
label: ISTPc
text:
I wrote a letter to researchers in the 
Soviet Union, asking about hypnopaedia,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity19
label: ISTPc
text: this is sleep-learning,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity20
label: ISTPc
text:
where you get a tape recorder, 
you put it beside your bed

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity21
label: ISTPc
text:
and it turns on 
in the middle of the night

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity22
label: ISTPc
text: when you're sleeping,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity23
label: ISTPc
text:
and you're supposed to be 
learning from this.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity24
label: ISTPc
text:
A good idea, 
unfortunately it doesn't work.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity25
label: ISTPc
text:
But, hypnopaedia did open the doors 
to research in other areas

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity26
label: ISTPc
text:
and we've had 
incredible discoveries about

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity27
label: ISTPc
text:
learning that began 
with that first question.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity28
label: ISTPc
text:
I went on from there to become 
passionate about psychology

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity29
label: ISTPc
text:
and I have been involved in psychology
in many different ways

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity30
label: ISTPc
text:
for the rest of my life 
up until this point.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity31
label: ISTPc
text: In 1981, I took myself to China

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity32
label: ISTPc
text:
and I decided that I was going to be 
native level in Chinese inside two years.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity33
label: ISTPc
text:
Now, you need to understand that 
in 1981, everybody thought

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity34
label: ISTPc
text: Chinese was really, really difficult

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity35
label: ISTPc
text:
and that a Westerner 
could study for 10 years or more

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity36
label: ISTPc
text: and never really get very good at it.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity37
label: ISTPc
text: And I also went in with a different idea

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity38
label: ISTPc
text: which was: taking all of the conclusions

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity39
label: ISTPc
text:
from psychological research 
up to that point

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity40
label: ISTPc
text:
and applying them 
to the learning process.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity41
label: ISTPc
text:
What was really cool was that in six 
months I was fluent in Mandarin Chinese

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity42
label: ISTPc
text:
and it took a little bit longer 
to get up to native.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity43
label: ISTPc
text:
But I looked around and I saw all of 
these people from different countries

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity44
label: ISTPc
text: struggling terribly with Chinese,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity45
label: ISTPc
text:
I saw Chinese people struggling terribly 
to learn English and other languages,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity46
label: ISTPc
text: and so my question got refined down to:

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity47
label: ISTPc
text: How can you help a normal adult

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity48
label: ISTPc
text:
learn a new language 
quickly, easily and effectively?

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity49
label: ISTPc
text:
Now this is a really, really important 
question in today's world.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity50
label: ISTPc
text:
We have massive challenges 
with environment,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity51
label: ISTPc
text:
we have massive challenges 
with social dislocation,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity52
label: ISTPc
text: with wars, all sorts of things going on

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity53
label: ISTPc
text: and if we can't communicate,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity54
label: ISTPc
text:
we're really going to have difficulty 
solving these problems.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity55
label: ISTPc
text:
So we need to be able to speak 
each other's languages,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity56
label: ISTPc
text: this is really, really important.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity57
label: ISTPc
text: The question then is: How do you do that?

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity58
label: ISTPc
text: Well, it's actually really easy.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity59
label: ISTPc
text:
You look around for people 
who can already do it,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity60
label: ISTPc
text:
you look for situations 
where it's already working

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity61
label: ISTPc
text:
and then you identify the principles
and apply them.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity62
label: ISTPc
text:
It's called modelling and I've been 
looking at language learning

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity63
label: ISTPc
text:
and modelling language learning 
for about 15 to 20 years now.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity64
label: ISTPc
text:
And my conclusion, 
my observation from this is

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity65
label: ISTPc
text:
that any adult can learn a second 
language to fluency inside six months.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity66
label: ISTPc
text:
Now when I say this, most people 
think I'm crazy, this is not possible.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity67
label: ISTPc
text:
So let me remind everybody of 
the history of human progress,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity68
label: ISTPc
text: it's all about expanding our limits.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity69
label: ISTPc
text:
In 1950, everybody believed that running 
one mile in four minutes was impossible,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity70
label: ISTPc
text: and then Roger Bannister did it in 1956

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity71
label: ISTPc
text:
and from there 
it's got shorter and shorter.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity72
label: ISTPc
text:
100 years ago everybody believed that 
heavy stuff doesn't fly.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity73
label: ISTPc
text: Except it does and we all know this.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity74
label: ISTPc
text: How does heavy stuff fly?

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity75
label: ISTPc
text:
We reorganise the material 
using principles that we have learned

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity76
label: ISTPc
text: from observing nature, birds in this case.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity77
label: ISTPc
text: And today we've gone even further...

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity78
label: ISTPc
text:
We've gone even further, 
so you can fly a car.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity79
label: ISTPc
text:
You can buy one of these 
for a couple 100.000 US dollars.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity80
label: ISTPc
text: We now have cars in the world that fly.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity81
label: ISTPc
text:
And there's a different way to fly 
which we've learned from squirrels.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity82
label: ISTPc
text:
So all you need to do is copy 
what a flying squirrel does,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity83
label: ISTPc
text:
build a suit called a wing suit and 
off you go, you can fly like a squirrel.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity84
label: ISTPc
text:
Now most people, a lot of people, 
I wouldn't say everybody

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity85
label: ISTPc
text: but a lot of people think they can't draw.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity86
label: ISTPc
text:
However there are some key principles, 
five principles, that you can apply

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity87
label: ISTPc
text:
to learning to draw and you can 
actually learn to draw in five days.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity88
label: ISTPc
text:
So, if you draw like this, you learn 
these principles for five days

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity89
label: ISTPc
text:
and apply them and after five days 
you can draw something like this.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity90
label: ISTPc
text:
Now I know this is true because 
that was my first drawing

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity91
label: ISTPc
text:
and after five days of applying these 
principles that was what I was able to do.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity92
label: ISTPc
text: And I looked at this and I went:

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity93
label: ISTPc
text:
"Wow, so that's how I look like 
when I'm concentrating so intensely

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity94
label: ISTPc
text: that my brain is exploding."

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity95
label: ISTPc
text: So, anybody can learn to draw in five days

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity96
label: ISTPc
text: and in the same way, with the same logic,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity97
label: ISTPc
text:
anybody can learn a second language
in six months.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity98
label: ISTPc
text:
How? There are five principles
and seven actions.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity99
label: ISTPc
text:
There may be a few more 
but these are absolutely core.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity100
label: ISTPc
text:
And before I get into those 
I just want to talk about two myths,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity101
label: ISTPc
text: I want to dispel two myths.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity102
label: ISTPc
text: The first is that you need talent.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity103
label: ISTPc
text: Let me tell you about Zoe.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity104
label: ISTPc
text:
Zoe came from Australia, went to Holland, 
was trying to learn Dutch,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity105
label: ISTPc
text:
struggling extremely, extremely... 
a great deal

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity106
label: ISTPc
text:
and finally people were saying: 
"You're completely useless,"

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity107
label: ISTPc
text:
"you're not talented," "give up," 
"you're a waste of time"

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity108
label: ISTPc
text: and she was very, very depressed.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity109
label: ISTPc
text:
And then she came across 
these five principles,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity110
label: ISTPc
text: she moved to Brazil and she applied them

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity111
label: ISTPc
text:
and in six months 
she was fluent in Portuguese,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity112
label: ISTPc
text: so talent doesn't matter.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity113
label: ISTPc
text:
People also think that immersion in a new 
country is the way to learn a language.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity114
label: ISTPc
text:
But look around Hong Kong, 
look at all the westerners

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity115
label: ISTPc
text:
who've been here for 10 years, 
who don't speak a word of Chinese.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity116
label: ISTPc
text:
Look at all the Chinese living in 
America, Britain, Australia, Canada

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity117
label: ISTPc
text:
have been there 10, 20 years 
and they don't speak any English.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity118
label: ISTPc
text: Immersion per se does not work.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity119
label: ISTPc
text:
Why? Because a drowning man 
cannot learn to swim.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity120
label: ISTPc
text:
When you don't speak a language, 
you're like a baby.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity121
label: ISTPc
text: And if you drop yourself into a context

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity122
label: ISTPc
text:
which is all adults talking about stuff 
over your head, you won't learn.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity123
label: ISTPc
text:
So, what are the five principles 
that you need to pay attention to?

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity124
label: ISTPc
text: First: the four words,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity125
label: ISTPc
text: attention, meaning, relevance and memory,

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity126
label: ISTPc
text:
and these interconnect in very, 
very important ways.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity127
label: ISTPc
text:
Especially when you're talking 
about learning.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity128
label: ISTPc
text:
Come with me on a journey 
through a forest.

id: ISTPc_How to learn any language in six months | Chris Lonsdale | TEDxLingnanUniversity129
label: ISTPc
text: You go on a walk through a forest
