text: incredible changes and up here on the

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose0
label: ENFJc
text: Let's play a game.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose1
label: ENFJc
text: Imagine that you are in Las Vegas,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose2
label: ENFJc
text: in a casino,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose3
label: ENFJc
text:
and you decide to play a game
on one of the casino's computers,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose4
label: ENFJc
text:
just like you might play
solitaire or chess.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose5
label: ENFJc
text:
The computer can make moves
in the game, just like a human player.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose6
label: ENFJc
text: This is a coin game.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose7
label: ENFJc
text: It starts with a coin showing heads,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose8
label: ENFJc
text: and the computer will play first.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose9
label: ENFJc
text: It can choose to flip the coin or not,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose10
label: ENFJc
text: but you don't get to see the outcome.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose11
label: ENFJc
text: Next, it's your turn.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose12
label: ENFJc
text:
You can also choose
to flip the coin or not,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose13
label: ENFJc
text:
and your move will not be revealed
to your opponent, the computer.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose14
label: ENFJc
text:
Finally, the computer plays again,
and can flip the coin or not,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose15
label: ENFJc
text: and after these three rounds,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose16
label: ENFJc
text: the coin is revealed,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose17
label: ENFJc
text: and if it is heads, the computer wins,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose18
label: ENFJc
text: if it's tails, you win.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose19
label: ENFJc
text: So it's a pretty simple game,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose20
label: ENFJc
text:
and if everybody plays honestly,
and the coin is fair,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose21
label: ENFJc
text:
then you have a 50 percent chance
of winning this game.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose22
label: ENFJc
text: And to confirm that,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose23
label: ENFJc
text:
I asked my students to play
this game on our computers,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose24
label: ENFJc
text: and after many, many tries,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose25
label: ENFJc
text:
their winning rate ended up
being 50 percent, or close to 50 percent,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose26
label: ENFJc
text: as expected.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose27
label: ENFJc
text: Sounds like a boring game, right?

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose28
label: ENFJc
text:
But what if you could play this game
on a quantum computer?

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose29
label: ENFJc
text:
Now, Las Vegas casinos
do not have quantum computers,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose30
label: ENFJc
text: as far as I know,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose31
label: ENFJc
text:
but IBM has built
a working quantum computer.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose32
label: ENFJc
text: Here it is.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose33
label: ENFJc
text: But what is a quantum computer?

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose34
label: ENFJc
text: Well, quantum physics describes

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose35
label: ENFJc
text:
the behavior of atoms
and fundamental particles,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose36
label: ENFJc
text: like electrons and photons.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose37
label: ENFJc
text: So a quantum computer operates

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose38
label: ENFJc
text:
by controlling the behavior
of these particles,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose39
label: ENFJc
text:
but in a way that is completely different
from our regular computers.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose40
label: ENFJc
text:
So a quantum computer
is not just a more powerful version

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose41
label: ENFJc
text: of our current computers,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose42
label: ENFJc
text:
just like a light bulb
is not a more powerful candle.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose43
label: ENFJc
text:
You cannot build a light bulb
by building better and better candles.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose44
label: ENFJc
text: A light bulb is a different technology,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose45
label: ENFJc
text: based on deeper scientific understanding.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose46
label: ENFJc
text:
Similarly, a quantum computer
is a new kind of device,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose47
label: ENFJc
text: based on the science of quantum physics,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose48
label: ENFJc
text:
and just like a light bulb
transformed society,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose49
label: ENFJc
text:
quantum computers
have the potential to impact

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose50
label: ENFJc
text: so many aspects of our lives,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose51
label: ENFJc
text:
including our security needs,
our health care and even the internet.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose52
label: ENFJc
text:
So companies all around the world
are working to build these devices,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose53
label: ENFJc
text:
and to see what
the excitement is all about,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose54
label: ENFJc
text: let's play our game on a quantum computer.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose55
label: ENFJc
text:
So I can log into IBM's
quantum computer from right here,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose56
label: ENFJc
text: which means I can play the game remotely,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose57
label: ENFJc
text: and so can you.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose58
label: ENFJc
text:
To make this happen, you may remember
getting an email ahead of time, from TED,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose59
label: ENFJc
text:
asking you whether you would choose
to flip the coin or not,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose60
label: ENFJc
text: if you played the game.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose61
label: ENFJc
text:
Well, actually, we asked you to choose
between a circle or a square.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose62
label: ENFJc
text:
You didn't know it, but your choice
of circle meant "flip the coin,"

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose63
label: ENFJc
text:
and your choice of square
was "don't flip."

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose64
label: ENFJc
text: We received 372 responses.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose65
label: ENFJc
text: Thank you.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose66
label: ENFJc
text:
That means we can play 372 games
against the quantum computer

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose67
label: ENFJc
text: using your choices.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose68
label: ENFJc
text: And it's a pretty fast game to play,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose69
label: ENFJc
text: so I can show you the results right here.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose70
label: ENFJc
text: Unfortunately, you didn't do very well.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose71
label: ENFJc
text: (Laughter)

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose72
label: ENFJc
text:
The quantum computer won
almost every game.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose73
label: ENFJc
text:
It lost a few only because
of operational errors in the computer.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose74
label: ENFJc
text: (Laughter)

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose75
label: ENFJc
text:
So how did it achieve
this amazing winning streak?

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose76
label: ENFJc
text: It seems like magic or cheating,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose77
label: ENFJc
text:
but actually, it's just
quantum physics in action.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose78
label: ENFJc
text: Here's how it works.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose79
label: ENFJc
text:
A regular computer simulates
heads or tails of a coin as a bit,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose80
label: ENFJc
text: a zero or a one,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose81
label: ENFJc
text:
or a current flipping on and off
inside your computer chip.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose82
label: ENFJc
text:
A quantum computer
is completely different.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose83
label: ENFJc
text:
A quantum bit has a more fluid,
nonbinary identity.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose84
label: ENFJc
text:
It can exist in a superposition,
or a combination of zero and one,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose85
label: ENFJc
text:
with some probability of being zero
and some probability of being one.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose86
label: ENFJc
text:
In other words,
its identity is on a spectrum.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose87
label: ENFJc
text:
For example, it could have
a 70 percent chance of being zero

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose88
label: ENFJc
text: and a 30 percent chance of being one

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose89
label: ENFJc

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose90
label: ENFJc
text: The possibilities are endless.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose91
label: ENFJc
text: The key idea here

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose92
label: ENFJc
text:
is that we have to give up
on precise values of zero and one

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose93
label: ENFJc
text: and allow for some uncertainty.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose94
label: ENFJc
text: So during the game,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose95
label: ENFJc
text:
the quantum computer creates
this fluid combination of heads and tails,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose96
label: ENFJc
text: zero and one,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose97
label: ENFJc
text: so that no matter what the player does,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose98
label: ENFJc
text: flip or no flip,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose99
label: ENFJc
text: the superposition remains intact.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose100
label: ENFJc
text:
It's kind of like stirring
a mixture of two fluids.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose101
label: ENFJc
text:
Whether or not you stir,
the fluids remain in a mixture,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose102
label: ENFJc
text: but in its final move,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose103
label: ENFJc
text:
the quantum computer
can unmix the zero and one,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose104
label: ENFJc
text:
perfectly recovering heads
so that you lose every time.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose105
label: ENFJc
text: (Laughter)

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose106
label: ENFJc
text:
If you think this is all a bit weird,
you are absolutely right.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose107
label: ENFJc
text:
Regular coins do not exist
in combinations of heads and tails.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose108
label: ENFJc
text:
We do not experience
this fluid quantum reality

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose109
label: ENFJc
text: in our everyday lives.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose110
label: ENFJc
text: So if you are confused by quantum,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose111
label: ENFJc
text: don't worry, you're getting it.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose112
label: ENFJc
text: (Laughter)

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose113
label: ENFJc
text:
But even though we don't experience
quantum strangeness,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose114
label: ENFJc
text:
we can see its very real
effects in action.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose115
label: ENFJc
text: You've seen the data for yourself.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose116
label: ENFJc
text: The quantum computer won

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose117
label: ENFJc
text:
because it harnessed
superposition and uncertainty,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose118
label: ENFJc
text: and these quantum properties are powerful,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose119
label: ENFJc
text: not just to win coin games,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose120
label: ENFJc
text:
but also to build
future quantum technologies.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose121
label: ENFJc
text:
So let me give you three examples
of potential applications

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose122
label: ENFJc
text: that could change our lives.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose123
label: ENFJc
text:
First of all, quantum uncertainty
could be used to create private keys

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose124
label: ENFJc
text:
for encrypting messages
sent from one location to another

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose125
label: ENFJc
text:
so that hackers could not
secretly copy the key perfectly,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose126
label: ENFJc
text: because of quantum uncertainty.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose127
label: ENFJc
text:
They would have to break
the laws of quantum physics

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose128
label: ENFJc
text: to hack the key.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose129
label: ENFJc
text:
So this kind of unbreakable encryption
is already being tested by banks

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose130
label: ENFJc
text: and other institutions worldwide.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose131
label: ENFJc
text:
Today, we use more than 17 billion
connected devices globally.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose132
label: ENFJc
text:
Just imagine the impact quantum encryption
could have in the future.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose133
label: ENFJc
text:
Secondly, quantum technologies could also
transform health care and medicine.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose134
label: ENFJc
text:
For example, the design and analysis
of molecules for drug development

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose135
label: ENFJc
text: is a challenging problem today,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose136
label: ENFJc
text:
and that's because
exactly describing and calculating

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose137
label: ENFJc
text:
all of the quantum properties
of all the atoms in the molecule

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose138
label: ENFJc
text:
is a computationally difficult task,
even for our supercomputers.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose139
label: ENFJc
text: But a quantum computer could do better,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose140
label: ENFJc
text:
because it operates using
the same quantum properties

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose141
label: ENFJc
text: as the molecule it's trying to simulate.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose142
label: ENFJc
text:
So future large-scale quantum
simulations for drug development

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose143
label: ENFJc
text:
could perhaps lead to treatments
for diseases like Alzheimer's,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose144
label: ENFJc
text: which affects thousands of lives.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose145
label: ENFJc
text:
And thirdly, my favorite
quantum application

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose146
label: ENFJc
text:
is teleportation of information
from one location to another

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose147
label: ENFJc
text:
without physically transmitting
the information.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose148
label: ENFJc
text: Sounds like sci-fi, but it is possible,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose149
label: ENFJc
text:
because these fluid identities
of the quantum particles

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose150
label: ENFJc
text: can get entangled across space and time

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose151
label: ENFJc
text:
in such a way that when you change
something about one particle,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose152
label: ENFJc
text: it can impact the other,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose153
label: ENFJc
text:
and that creates
a channel for teleportation.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose154
label: ENFJc
text:
It's already been demonstrated
in research labs

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose155
label: ENFJc
text:
and could be part
of a future quantum internet.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose156
label: ENFJc
text: We don't have such a network as yet,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose157
label: ENFJc
text:
but my team is working
on these possibilities,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose158
label: ENFJc
text:
by simulating a quantum network
on a quantum computer.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose159
label: ENFJc
text:
So we have designed and implemented
some interesting new protocols

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose160
label: ENFJc
text:
such as teleportation
among different users in the network

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose161
label: ENFJc
text: and efficient data transmission

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose162
label: ENFJc
text: and even secure voting.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose163
label: ENFJc
text:
So it's a lot of fun for me,
being a quantum physicist.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose164
label: ENFJc
text: I highly recommend it.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose165
label: ENFJc
text: (Laughter)

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose166
label: ENFJc
text:
We get to be explorers
in a quantum wonderland.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose167
label: ENFJc
text:
Who knows what applications
we will discover next.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose168
label: ENFJc
text: We must tread carefully and responsibly

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose169
label: ENFJc
text: as we build our quantum future.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose170
label: ENFJc
text: And for me, personally,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose171
label: ENFJc
text:
I don't see quantum physics as a tool
just to build quantum computers.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose172
label: ENFJc
text:
I see quantum computers as a way
for us to probe the mysteries of nature

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose173
label: ENFJc
text:
and reveal more about this hidden world
outside of our experiences.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose174
label: ENFJc
text: How amazing that we humans,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose175
label: ENFJc
text:
with our relatively limited
access to the universe,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose176
label: ENFJc
text: can still see far beyond our horizons

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose177
label: ENFJc
text:
just using our imagination
and our ingenuity.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose178
label: ENFJc
text: And the universe rewards us

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose179
label: ENFJc
text:
by showing us how incredibly
interesting and surprising it is.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose180
label: ENFJc
text: The future is fundamentally uncertain,

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose181
label: ENFJc
text: and to me, that is certainly exciting.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose182
label: ENFJc
text: Thank you.

id: ENFJc_A beginner's guide to quantum computing | Shohini Ghose183
label: ENFJc
text: (Applause)

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm0
label: ISTPc
text:
Translator: Florencia Bracamonte
Reviewer: Tanya Cushman

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm1
label: ISTPc
text:
In 2009, a man, a journalist
by the name Rob Walker,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm2
label: ISTPc
text: wanted to find out this:

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm3
label: ISTPc
text:
Is storytelling really
the most powerful tool of all?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm4
label: ISTPc
text: And in order to do this,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm5
label: ISTPc
text:
he went on his computer,
and he bought 200 objects from eBay.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm6
label: ISTPc
text:
And the average price of the objects
was about one dollar.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm7
label: ISTPc
text:
He then called 200 authors,
and he asked them,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm8
label: ISTPc
text:
"Hey, would you like to be part
of the 'significant object study'?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm9
label: ISTPc
text:
Which means that I would like you
to write a story to one of the objects."

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm10
label: ISTPc
text: And 200 authors said yes.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm11
label: ISTPc
text:
So there he had 200 objects,
he had 200 stories,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm12
label: ISTPc
text:
and I assume that it was
with nail-biting anticipation

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm13
label: ISTPc
text:
that he went on eBay again
with all the 200 objects.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm14
label: ISTPc
text:
Would there be a difference?
Would there be a change?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm15
label: ISTPc
text: Do you think there was a change?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm16
label: ISTPc
text: One of the objects was this,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm17
label: ISTPc
text: this beautiful horse's head.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm18
label: ISTPc
text: There we go.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm19
label: ISTPc
text: The beautiful horse's head.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm20
label: ISTPc
text:
Now, this beautiful horse's head
was bought for 99

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm21
label: ISTPc
text:
and was sold, when the story
was added, for $62.95.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm22
label: ISTPc
text: (Laughter)

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm23
label: ISTPc
text: That is a slight increase of 6395%.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm24
label: ISTPc
text: So, was this a one-off situation?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm25
label: ISTPc
text: Not really,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm26
label: ISTPc
text:
because he bought the 200 objects
for a total of $129,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm27
label: ISTPc
text: selling them for $8000.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm28
label: ISTPc
text: Now, that's insane.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm29
label: ISTPc
text:
But you know what's even more
intellectually challenging to understand?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm30
label: ISTPc
text: How can you and I

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm31
label: ISTPc
text:
go to the movies and pay good money
to watch movies like James Bond,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm32
label: ISTPc
text: [that] are absolutely unrealistic?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm33
label: ISTPc
text:
And we sit there;
we enjoy the movie.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm34
label: ISTPc
text: And some of us, we really enjoy the movie.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm35
label: ISTPc
text:
And we leave the theater,
going like, "God, what a man!

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm36
label: ISTPc
text: I would like to be more like him.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm37
label: ISTPc
text:
I'd like to walk like him.
I'd like to talk like him.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm38
label: ISTPc
text: I like Bond.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm39
label: ISTPc
text: (Laughter)

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm40
label: ISTPc
text: I wonder how I could be more like Bond."

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm41
label: ISTPc
text:
And then this weird revelation
hits you like from nowhere,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm42
label: ISTPc
text:
and you come up with a brilliant idea
to walk to a watchmaker shop.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm43
label: ISTPc
text:
And wow! It just happens
to be an Omega watch in that shop

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm44
label: ISTPc
text:
that resembles the one
that Bond was wearing in the movie.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm45
label: ISTPc
text:
And you pay $10,000
to put that watch on your wrist.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm46
label: ISTPc
text:
And you leave that store
feeling more like Bond.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm47
label: ISTPc
text: How is that possible?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm48
label: ISTPc
text:
PQ Media tells us
that 10.5 billion dollars

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm49
label: ISTPc
text:
is turned over in product placement
revenue every single year.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm50
label: ISTPc
text:
How is it possible for you
to be so easily tricked

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm51
label: ISTPc
text: by something so simple as a story?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm52
label: ISTPc
text: Because you are tricked.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm53
label: ISTPc
text: Well, it all comes down to one core thing,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm54
label: ISTPc
text: and that is emotional investment.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm55
label: ISTPc
text:
The more emotionally invested you are
in anything in your life,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm56
label: ISTPc
text:
the less critical and the less
objectively observant you become.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm57
label: ISTPc
text:
And the greatest
emotional investment of all

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm58
label: ISTPc
text: is falling in love.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm59
label: ISTPc
text:
Now, falling in love
resembles a good story.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm60
label: ISTPc
text:
Do you remember
the last time you fell in love?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm61
label: ISTPc
text:
Yeah? Good for you.
It's a beautiful feeling, isn't it?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm62
label: ISTPc
text: (Laughter)

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm63
label: ISTPc
text:
Do you remember how you longed
and how you yearned and how you dreamt?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm64
label: ISTPc
text:
Then you looked at her,
and maybe you thought,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm65
label: ISTPc
text: "God, I love the way you chew that apple -

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm66
label: ISTPc
text: so crunchy.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm67
label: ISTPc
text: (Laughter)

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm68
label: ISTPc
text:
And the way you slurp that tea,
just over the edge, you know.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm69
label: ISTPc
text: Oh, it's so sexy.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm70
label: ISTPc
text: Love it!"

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm71
label: ISTPc
text:
And then about 13 months later,
when you biochemically fall out of love -

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm72
label: ISTPc
text:
13 months later, on an average,
you fall out of love -

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm73
label: ISTPc
text:
suddenly you find yourself
sitting in the sofa, and you go,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm74
label: ISTPc
text:
"Jesus Christ, where
did this thing come from?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm75
label: ISTPc
text: Oh my God! And where are my friends?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm76
label: ISTPc
text: This is a weird thing."

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm77
label: ISTPc
text:
Then suddenly you hear a sound;
you go like, "What's that?"

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm78
label: ISTPc
text:
You go over to the kitchen,
and you look, and you go like,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm79
label: ISTPc
text:
"Oh, it's you!
You're eating an apple there.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm80
label: ISTPc
text:
Could you just keep that down
just a little bit?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm81
label: ISTPc
text: You're kind of spraying the table there.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm82
label: ISTPc
text: Please, please don't."

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm83
label: ISTPc
text: And you sit down comfortably again,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm84
label: ISTPc
text: and just a minute later,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm85
label: ISTPc
text:
you hear somebody drinking tea
from the kitchen, going (Slurp).

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm86
label: ISTPc
text: And suddenly, this is all annoying to you.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm87
label: ISTPc
text: Have you been there?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm88
label: ISTPc
text: Sadly enough,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm89
label: ISTPc
text: 13 months later,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm90
label: ISTPc
text:
our critical thinking and our cortex
comes home from a one-year-long vacation,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm91
label: ISTPc
text: and we start questioning things.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm92
label: ISTPc
text:
During those 13 months, what happened
was that your brain was flooded

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm93
label: ISTPc
text:
with neurotransmitters and hormones
hijacking your cortex,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm94
label: ISTPc
text:
throwing your objectively
observant skills out of the window.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm95
label: ISTPc
text:
And the thing with storytelling
is that the same thing can happen.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm96
label: ISTPc
text:
In stories, the same hormones
and neurotransmitters can be released.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm97
label: ISTPc
text:
Hormones like vasopressin, oxytocin,
serotonin, dopamine, endorphins.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm98
label: ISTPc
text: And you know what?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm99
label: ISTPc
text:
That's what I would like to do
during my talk.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm100
label: ISTPc
text:
I would like to induce
three hormones into your brain.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm101
label: ISTPc
text:
I call it "the angels' cocktail,"
so it's a nice cocktail.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm102
label: ISTPc
text:
I would like to start with radically
increasing your dopamine levels.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm103
label: ISTPc
text: And I need your consent on this.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm104
label: ISTPc
text: Is it okay?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm105
label: ISTPc
text: Cool.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm106
label: ISTPc
text:
And if you don't like the idea of that,
you'll just have to cover your ears.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm107
label: ISTPc
text: So, dopamine. This is what it looks like.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm108
label: ISTPc
text:
And when you have that in your blood,
these are the beautiful effects:

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm109
label: ISTPc
text:
you get more focus, more motivation,
and you remember things in a better way.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm110
label: ISTPc
text:
So what does dopamine feel like?
It feels like this.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm111
label: ISTPc
text:
About six years ago, I received
a phone call from a woman

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm112
label: ISTPc
text:
who represented one of the biggest
training companies in Scandinavia,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm113
label: ISTPc
text: and she said, "Hey, David!

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm114
label: ISTPc
text:
We've got a lot of trainers
in presentation skills and in rhetorics,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm115
label: ISTPc
text:
and we'd like to increase
the level of all of these,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm116
label: ISTPc
text: and we think you are a perfect pick.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm117
label: ISTPc
text: Would you like to come to a meeting?"

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm118
label: ISTPc
text: I'm like, "Wow, I'm honored. I'd love to."

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm119
label: ISTPc
text:
And I come up to Stockholm,
and I'm going to their office,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm120
label: ISTPc
text:
and just as I am going
to pull the handle down,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm121
label: ISTPc
text: what I don't know then

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm122
label: ISTPc
text:
is that I'm walking into
one of the absolute worst meetings

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm123
label: ISTPc
text: I'm ever going to have in my life.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm124
label: ISTPc
text: But I don't know that yet, so it's okay.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm125
label: ISTPc
text: I open the door, and I meet this woman.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm126
label: ISTPc
text: Her name is Liana.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm127
label: ISTPc
text:
And hurriedly she says,
"David, just so you know,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm128
label: ISTPc
text:
I'm not the one you're having
this meeting with;

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm129
label: ISTPc
text:
you're going to have it
with three gentlemen, further on here."

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm130
label: ISTPc
text:
And I'm like, "Okay,
that's a bit strange."

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm131
label: ISTPc
text:
Usually you know who
you're going to have the meeting with.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm132
label: ISTPc
text:
Then she progresses
with a bit of chit-chatting,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm133
label: ISTPc
text:
and then suddenly she says,
"Are you ready now?"

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm134
label: ISTPc
text:
And I'm like, "Yeah,
what should I be ready for?"

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm135
label: ISTPc
text:
She says, "Just so you know -
Can you see the room over there?"

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm136
label: ISTPc
text: And I go like, "Yes, I can see it."

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm137
label: ISTPc
text:
"Well, in that room
you have the three gentlemen.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm138
label: ISTPc
text:
Just so you know, they're all
majority owners of this company.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm139
label: ISTPc
text: They've all got an ex-military background,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm140
label: ISTPc
text:
and none of them wants the training
that you are going to pitch."

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm141
label: ISTPc
text: (Laughter)

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm142
label: ISTPc
text: I'm like, "Come on!

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm143
label: ISTPc
text: Why am I here?"

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm144
label: ISTPc
text:
And it's like, "Well,
all the trainers want this,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm145
label: ISTPc
text: but the management are on too high horses.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm146
label: ISTPc
text: They can't see that they need it.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm147
label: ISTPc
text: So it's pretty simple.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm148
label: ISTPc
text:
The only thing you have to do
is go in there and kind of, you know,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm149
label: ISTPc
text: just prove the opposite."

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm150
label: ISTPc
text:
I'm like, "Yeah, that sounds
simple, doesn't it?"

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm151
label: ISTPc
text:
And I can remember myself,
I'm walking towards this office,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm152
label: ISTPc
text:
my sweat is coming down
my palms, my heart is racing,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm153
label: ISTPc
text: and just halfway there, she calls my name.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm154
label: ISTPc
text: And I still, to this day,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm155
label: ISTPc
text:
don't know if this woman
is sadomasochistic

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm156
label: ISTPc
text: or just downright unintelligent.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm157
label: ISTPc
text:
Because she calls my name,
and she goes like, "David!"

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm158
label: ISTPc
text:
It's like I'm going to get the tip
or something like that,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm159
label: ISTPc
text: so I turn around to ask her,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm160
label: ISTPc
text: and she says the following -

label: ISTPc
text:
And if I don't tell you
what she says there, is that annoying?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm162
label: ISTPc
text: (Laughter)

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm163
label: ISTPc
text:
Well, actually, as an example,
I'm not going to do that.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm164
label: ISTPc
text:
I just wanted to prove to you
what it feels with high dopamine levels.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm165
label: ISTPc
text:
Would you say that
your focus was increased?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm166
label: ISTPc
text: Your attention was increased?

label: ISTPc
text:
You were creative;
you created situations around this,

label: ISTPc
text:
and you probably already figured out
what that room looked like, correct?

label: ISTPc
text:
And you'll remember that I
did that to you for quite a while.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm170
label: ISTPc
text: Now, the feeling you had there

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm171
label: ISTPc
text:
was high levels of dopamine,
which is beautiful.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm172
label: ISTPc
text: So how do you do that?

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm173
label: ISTPc
text: Well, what you do is you build suspense,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm174
label: ISTPc
text: you launch a cliffhanger,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm175
label: ISTPc
text: and the most beautiful thing of all

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm176
label: ISTPc
text:
is that all storytelling is,
per definition, dopamine-creating

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm177
label: ISTPc
text:
because it's always something
that we're waiting and expecting.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm178
label: ISTPc
text:
So just imagine, just by using
storytelling you can get those techniques.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm179
label: ISTPc
text:
You don't have to do
a cliffhanger like I did.

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm180
label: ISTPc
text: So that was the first hormone.

text: I'd now like to go to oxytocin.

label: ISTPc
text:
The beautiful effects
of oxytocin are the following:

text:
you become more generous,
you trust me more, and you bond to me.

And the little brother, who was

he was kind of really looking forward

label: ISTPc

And he had helped us
pick out the wallpaper,

id: ISTPc_The magical science of storytelling | David JP Phillips | TEDxStockholm196

He'd even saved his own pocket money

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #50
label: INTJc
text:
SIRAJ:
-Hello World, it's Siraj!

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #51
label: INTJc
text: In this video, we're gonna create a neural network

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #52
label: INTJc
text: that makes images become really trippy

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #53
label: INTJc
text: using Python and TensorFlow.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #54
label: INTJc
text: We humans have been using psychedelic drugs

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #55
label: INTJc
text: since prehistoric time.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #56
label: INTJc
text: -That wasn't a normal mushroom!

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #57
label: INTJc
text: They help manifest parts of our mind

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #58
label: INTJc
text: to conscious experience that wouldn't normally otherwise.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #59
label: INTJc
text: One of the most common experiences

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #510
label: INTJc
text: from psychedelics are trippy visuals.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #511
label: INTJc
text: People who have taken psychedelics

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #512
label: INTJc
text: repeatedly describe experiences of seeing

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #513
label: INTJc
text: both open-eyed and closed-eyed visuals.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #514
label: INTJc
text: But how? What are these drugs doing in our brain

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #515
label: INTJc
text: that makes us see things that aren't really there?

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #516
label: INTJc
text: The traditional way for us to find out

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #517
label: INTJc
text: is to test live human subjects tripping balls

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #518
label: INTJc
text: under an fMRI machine,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #519
label: INTJc
text: but recently, we've gotten artificial neural networks

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #520
label: INTJc
text: that do the same thing,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #521
label: INTJc
text: Google trained a neural network

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #522
label: INTJc
text: on a labeled dataset of images --

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #523
label: INTJc
text: everything from squirrels to temples --

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #524
label: INTJc
text: and as it trained on these images,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #525
label: INTJc
text: it built internal representations at each layer.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #526
label: INTJc
text: Eventually, the first two layers learned low-level features

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #527
label: INTJc
text: like lines and edges, and they got progressively more abstract

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #528
label: INTJc
text: so the last few layers were representations

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #529
label: INTJc
text: for faces and big shapes.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #530
label: INTJc
text: So when we visualize one of

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #531
label: INTJc
text: the higher-level representations it built,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #532
label: INTJc
text: we can see that it contains a mixture of features

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #533
label: INTJc
text: like the eyes of a dog and the head of a bird.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #534
label: INTJc
text: Eugh!

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #535
label: INTJc
text: And when they gave it a novel image

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #536
label: INTJc
text: and asked not to classify it

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #537
label: INTJc
text: but to maximize the similarity between the image

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #538
label: INTJc
text: and a representation at a particular layer,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #539
label: INTJc
text: the result was a very trippy image.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #540
label: INTJc
text: It all sounds very similar to the drug experience

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #541
label: INTJc
text: which is insane.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #542
label: INTJc
text: Our brains are carbon-based

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #543
label: INTJc
text: and they use chemical signals as messengers.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #544
label: INTJc
text: A neural network doesn't even exist

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #545
label: INTJc
text: in physical space at all.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #546
label: INTJc
text: It's an abstract concept being represented

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #547
label: INTJc
text: on binary silicon transistors.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #548
label: INTJc
text: There's no reason to expect that these two systems

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #549
label: INTJc
text: would develop the same mechanism

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #550
label: INTJc
text: for processing visual information.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #551
label: INTJc
text: Even with existing similarities,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #552
label: INTJc
text: natural selection is very different from using

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #553
label: INTJc
text: gradient descent to alter weights

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #554
label: INTJc
text: of connection between nodes.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #555
label: INTJc
text: Could it be that, somehow,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #556
label: INTJc
text: encoded in the fundamental rules of the universe

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #557
label: INTJc
text: there's this ideal way of doing object recognition?

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #558
label: INTJc
text:
TRINITY:
-What is he doing?

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #559
label: INTJc
text:
MORPHEUS:
-He's beginning to believe.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #560
label: INTJc
text:
SIRAJ (AS NEO):
-You're damn right, Morpheus.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #561
label: INTJc
text: -We're getting closer to understanding it every day,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #562
label: INTJc
text: and we can learn a lot about the brain

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #563
label: INTJc
text: including human development,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #564
label: INTJc
text: treatment for cognitive disabilities, and drug effects,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #565
label: INTJc
text: from studying artificial neural networks.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #566
label: INTJc
text: After we install our dependencies,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #567
label: INTJc
text: we're gonna replicate Google's Deep Dream code

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #568
label: INTJc
text: in TensorFlow, and then test it out on a novel image.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #569
label: INTJc
text: NumPy will be used to perform math calculations.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #570
label: INTJc
text: The 'partial' submodule of functools

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #571
label: INTJc
text: lets us create new versions of functions

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #572
label: INTJc
text: with one or more arguments filled in.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #573
label: INTJc
text: This is good for reusability,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #574
label: INTJc
text: which means less code to write.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #575
label: INTJc
text: Pillow is an imaging library,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #576
label: INTJc
text: and Image will help us modify our images.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #577
label: INTJc
text: TensorFlow is our machine learning library.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #578
label: INTJc
text: urllib will let us download data from the web.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #579
label: INTJc
text: os will let us use

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #580
label: INTJc
text: operating system-dependent functionality,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #581
label: INTJc
text: and ziptools [sic] will let us run FREE!

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #582
label: INTJc
text: No. It'll just let us unzip files.

label: INTJc
text: Our imports are already at the top of our script

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #584
label: INTJc
text: so we're going to download

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #585
label: INTJc
text: Google's pre-trained neural network,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #586
label: INTJc
text: create a TensorFlow session,

label: INTJc

label: INTJc
text: to enhance our input image,

label: INTJc

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #590
label: INTJc

label: INTJc

label: INTJc
text: and we can collect them all

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5146
label: INTJc
text: and store them in the 'feature_nums' variable.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5147
label: INTJc
text: Let's print them out and visualize what we've got

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5148
label: INTJc
text: in terminal first.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5149
label: INTJc
text: We can see our number of layers

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5150
label: INTJc
text: and the total number of feature channels right here.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5151
label: INTJc
text: Let's now pick a layer from our model

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5152
label: INTJc
text: that we're going to enhance.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5153
label: INTJc
text: We'll pick a lower-level layer

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5154
label: INTJc
text: and pick one of the feature channels to visualize.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5155
label: INTJc
text: It's time to load our input image

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5156
label: INTJc
text: using the Pillow Image submodule's open() method

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5157
label: INTJc
text: and store it in our image variable.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5158
label: INTJc
text: We'll format it accordingly using NumPy

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5159
label: INTJc
text: and perform Deep Dream on it

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5160
label: INTJc
text: with our render_deepdream() function

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5161
label: INTJc
text: with a focus on the layer we selected earlier.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5162
label: INTJc
text: In our Deep Dream function,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5163
label: INTJc
text: we can see a couple of our predefined hyperparameters.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5164
label: INTJc
text: We'll start by defining our optimization objective,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5165
label: INTJc
text: which is to reduce the mean of our input layer.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5166
label: INTJc
text: The gradients() function lets us compute

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5167
label: INTJc
text: the symbolic gradient of our optimized tensor

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5168
label: INTJc
text: with respect to our input tensor.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5169
label: INTJc
text: Now we can split our image into a number of octaves

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5170
label: INTJc
text: and say for each octave, let's resize it using NumPy

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5171
label: INTJc
text: and add it to our array of image octaves.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5172
label: INTJc
text: Then we can generate details octave by octave

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5173
label: INTJc
text: by iterating through each.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5174
label: INTJc
text: Random shapes are applied to the image

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5175
label: INTJc
text: to blur tile boundaries over multiple iterations

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5176
label: INTJc
text: using the calc_grad_tiled() function.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5177
label: INTJc
text: We're essentially applying gradient ascent here

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5178
label: INTJc
text: to maximize our loss function,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5179
label: INTJc
text: which merges our saved representation

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5180
label: INTJc
text: in this layer with our input image

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5181
label: INTJc
text: more and more every iteration.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5182
label: INTJc
text: So to break it down,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5183
label: INTJc
text: neural networks are a great test for learning

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5184
label: INTJc
text: about how the brain functions

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5185
label: INTJc
text: and responds to certain stimuli.

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5186
label: INTJc
text: They store increasingly abstract representations

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5187
label: INTJc
text: of what they learn in their layers,

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5188
label: INTJc
text: and we can create trippy images

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5189
label: INTJc

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5190
label: INTJc

id: INTJc_Deep Dream in TensorFlow - Learn Python for Data Science #5191
