id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker0
label: INTJc
text: Thank you very much.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker1
label: INTJc
text:
Well, I would like
to start with testicles.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker2
label: INTJc
text: (Laughter)

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker3
label: INTJc
text: Men who sleep five hours a night

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker4
label: INTJc
text:
have significantly smaller testicles
than those who sleep seven hours or more.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker5
label: INTJc
text: (Laughter)

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker6
label: INTJc
text:
In addition, men who routinely sleep
just four to five hours a night

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker7
label: INTJc
text: will have a level of testosterone

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker8
label: INTJc
text:
which is that of someone
10 years their senior.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker9
label: INTJc
text:
So a lack of sleep
will age a man by a decade

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker10
label: INTJc
text:
in terms of that critical
aspect of wellness.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker11
label: INTJc
text:
And we see equivalent impairments
in female reproductive health

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker12
label: INTJc
text: caused by a lack of sleep.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker13
label: INTJc
text:
This is the best news
that I have for you today.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker14
label: INTJc
text: (Laughter)

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker15
label: INTJc
text: From this point, it may only get worse.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker16
label: INTJc
text:
Not only will I tell you
about the wonderfully good things

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker17
label: INTJc
text: that happen when you get sleep,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker18
label: INTJc
text:
but the alarmingly bad things
that happen when you don't get enough,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker19
label: INTJc
text: both for your brain and for your body.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker20
label: INTJc
text: Let me start with the brain

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker21
label: INTJc
text: and the functions of learning and memory,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker22
label: INTJc
text:
because what we've discovered
over the past 10 or so years

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker23
label: INTJc
text: is that you need sleep after learning

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker24
label: INTJc
text:
to essentially hit the save button
on those new memories

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker25
label: INTJc
text: so that you don't forget.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker26
label: INTJc
text:
But recently, we discovered
that you also need sleep before learning

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker27
label: INTJc
text: to actually prepare your brain,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker28
label: INTJc
text: almost like a dry sponge

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker29
label: INTJc
text:
ready to initially soak up
new information.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker30
label: INTJc
text:
And without sleep,
the memory circuits of the brain

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker31
label: INTJc
text:
essentially become
waterlogged, as it were,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker32
label: INTJc
text: and you can't absorb new memories.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker33
label: INTJc
text: So let me show you the data.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker34
label: INTJc
text:
Here in this study, we decided
to test the hypothesis

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker35
label: INTJc
text:
that pulling the all-nighter
was a good idea.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker36
label: INTJc
text: So we took a group of individuals

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker37
label: INTJc
text:
and we assigned them
to one of two experimental groups:

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker38
label: INTJc
text:
a sleep group
and a sleep deprivation group.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker39
label: INTJc
text:
Now the sleep group, they're going to get
a full eight hours of slumber,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker40
label: INTJc
text:
but the deprivation group,
we're going to keep them awake

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker41
label: INTJc
text: in the laboratory, under full supervision.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker42
label: INTJc
text:
There's no naps or caffeine, by the way,
so it's miserable for everyone involved.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker43
label: INTJc
text: And then the next day,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker44
label: INTJc
text:
we're going to place those participants
inside an MRI scanner

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker45
label: INTJc
text:
and we're going to have them
try and learn a whole list of new facts

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker46
label: INTJc
text:
as we're taking snapshots
of brain activity.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker47
label: INTJc
text: And then we're going to test them

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker48
label: INTJc
text:
to see how effective
that learning has been.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker49
label: INTJc
text:
And that's what you're looking at
here on the vertical axis.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker50
label: INTJc
text:
And when you put
those two groups head to head,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker51
label: INTJc
text:
what you find is a quite significant,
40-percent deficit

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker52
label: INTJc
text:
in the ability of the brain
to make new memories without sleep.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker53
label: INTJc
text: I think this should be concerning,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker54
label: INTJc
text:
considering what we know
is happening to sleep

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker55
label: INTJc
text: in our education populations right now.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker56
label: INTJc
text: In fact, to put that in context,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker57
label: INTJc
text:
it would be the difference
in a child acing an exam

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker58
label: INTJc
text: versus failing it miserably -- 40 percent.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker59
label: INTJc
text:
And we've gone on to discover
what goes wrong within your brain

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker60
label: INTJc
text:
to produce these types
of learning disabilities.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker61
label: INTJc
text: And there's a structure that sits

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker62
label: INTJc
text:
on the left and the right side
of your brain, called the hippocampus.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker63
label: INTJc
text: And you can think of the hippocampus

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker64
label: INTJc
text:
almost like the informational
inbox of your brain.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker65
label: INTJc
text:
It's very good at receiving
new memory files

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker66
label: INTJc
text: and then holding on to them.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker67
label: INTJc
text: And when you look at this structure

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker68
label: INTJc
text:
in those people who'd had
a full night of sleep,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker69
label: INTJc
text:
we saw lots of healthy
learning-related activity.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker70
label: INTJc
text:
Yet in those people
who were sleep-deprived,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker71
label: INTJc
text:
we actually couldn't find
any significant signal whatsoever.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker72
label: INTJc
text:
So it's almost as though sleep deprivation
had shut down your memory inbox,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker73
label: INTJc
text:
and any new incoming files --
they were just being bounced.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker74
label: INTJc
text:
You couldn't effectively
commit new experiences to memory.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker75
label: INTJc
text:
So that's the bad that can happen
if I were to take sleep away from you,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker76
label: INTJc
text:
but let me just come back
to that control group for a second.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker77
label: INTJc
text:
Do you remember those folks
that got a full eight hours of sleep?

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker78
label: INTJc
text:
Well, we can ask
a very different question:

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker79
label: INTJc
text:
What is it about the physiological
quality of your sleep

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker80
label: INTJc
text: when you do get it

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker81
label: INTJc
text:
that restores and enhances
your memory and learning ability

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker82
label: INTJc
text: each and every day?

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker83
label: INTJc
text:
And by placing electrodes
all over the head,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker84
label: INTJc
text:
what we've discovered
is that there are big, powerful brainwaves

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker85
label: INTJc
text:
that happen during
the very deepest stages of sleep

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker86
label: INTJc
text: that have riding on top of them

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker87
label: INTJc
text:
these spectacular bursts
of electrical activity

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker88
label: INTJc
text: that we call sleep spindles.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker89
label: INTJc
text:
And it's the combined quality
of these deep-sleep brainwaves

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker90
label: INTJc
text:
that acts like a file-transfer
mechanism at night,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker91
label: INTJc
text:
shifting memories from a short-term
vulnerable reservoir

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker92
label: INTJc
text:
to a more permanent long-term
storage site within the brain,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker93
label: INTJc
text:
and therefore protecting them,
making them safe.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker94
label: INTJc
text: And it is important that we understand

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker95
label: INTJc
text:
what during sleep actually transacts
these memory benefits,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker96
label: INTJc
text:
because there are real medical
and societal implications.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker97
label: INTJc
text: And let me just tell you about one area

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker98
label: INTJc
text:
that we've moved this work
out into, clinically,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker99
label: INTJc
text:
which is the context of aging
and dementia.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker100
label: INTJc
text:
Because it's of course no secret
that, as we get older,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker101
label: INTJc
text:
our learning and memory abilities
begin to fade and decline.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker102
label: INTJc
text: But what we've also discovered

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker103
label: INTJc
text:
is that a physiological signature of aging
is that your sleep gets worse,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker104
label: INTJc
text:
especially that deep quality of sleep
that I was just discussing.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker105
label: INTJc
text:
And only last year,
we finally published evidence

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker106
label: INTJc
text:
that these two things,
they're not simply co-occurring,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker107
label: INTJc
text: they are significantly interrelated.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker108
label: INTJc
text:
And it suggests
that the disruption of deep sleep

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker109
label: INTJc
text: is an underappreciated factor

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker110
label: INTJc
text:
that is contributing
to cognitive decline or memory decline

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker111
label: INTJc
text:
in aging, and most recently
we've discovered,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker112
label: INTJc
text: in Alzheimer's disease as well.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker113
label: INTJc
text:
Now, I know this is remarkably
depressing news.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker114
label: INTJc
text: It's in the mail. It's coming at you.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker115
label: INTJc
text:
But there's a potential
silver lining here.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker116
label: INTJc
text:
Unlike many of the other factors
that we know are associated with aging,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker117
label: INTJc
text:
for example changes
in the physical structure of the brain,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker118
label: INTJc
text: that's fiendishly difficult to treat.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker119
label: INTJc
text:
But that sleep is a missing piece
in the explanatory puzzle

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker120
label: INTJc
text: of aging and Alzheimer's is exciting

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker121
label: INTJc
text:
because we may be able
to do something about it.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker122
label: INTJc
text:
And one way that we are
approaching this at my sleep center

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker123
label: INTJc
text:
is not by using
sleeping pills, by the way.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker124
label: INTJc
text:
Unfortunately, they are blunt instruments
that do not produce naturalistic sleep.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker125
label: INTJc
text:
Instead, we're actually developing
a method based on this.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker126
label: INTJc
text:
It's called direct current
brain stimulation.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker127
label: INTJc
text:
You insert a small amount
of voltage into the brain,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker128
label: INTJc
text: so small you typically don't feel it,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker129
label: INTJc
text: but it has a measurable impact.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker130
label: INTJc
text:
Now if you apply this stimulation
during sleep in young, healthy adults,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker131
label: INTJc
text:
as if you're sort of singing in time
with those deep-sleep brainwaves,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker132
label: INTJc
text:
not only can you amplify
the size of those deep-sleep brainwaves,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker133
label: INTJc
text:
but in doing so, we can almost
double the amount of memory benefit

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker134
label: INTJc
text: that you get from sleep.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker135
label: INTJc
text:
The question now
is whether we can translate

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker136
label: INTJc
text:
this same affordable,
potentially portable piece of technology

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker137
label: INTJc
text: into older adults and those with dementia.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker138
label: INTJc
text:
Can we restore back
some healthy quality of deep sleep,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker139
label: INTJc
text:
and in doing so, can we salvage
aspects of their learning

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker140
label: INTJc
text: and memory function?

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker141
label: INTJc
text: That is my real hope now.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker142
label: INTJc
text:
That's one of our moon-shot
goals, as it were.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker143
label: INTJc
text:
So that's an example
of sleep for your brain,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker144
label: INTJc
text:
but sleep is just
as essential for your body.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker145
label: INTJc
text:
We've already spoken about sleep loss
and your reproductive system.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker146
label: INTJc
text:
Or I could tell you about sleep loss
and your cardiovascular system,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker147
label: INTJc
text: and that all it takes is one hour.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker148
label: INTJc
text:
Because there is a global experiment
performed on 1.6 billion people

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker149
label: INTJc
text: across 70 countries twice a year,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker150
label: INTJc
text: and it's called daylight saving time.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker151
label: INTJc
text:
Now, in the spring,
when we lose one hour of sleep,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker152
label: INTJc
text:
we see a subsequent 24-percent increase
in heart attacks that following day.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker153
label: INTJc
text:
In the autumn,
when we gain an hour of sleep,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker154
label: INTJc
text:
we see a 21-percent
reduction in heart attacks.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker155
label: INTJc
text: Isn't that incredible?

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker156
label: INTJc
text:
And you see exactly the same profile
for car crashes, road traffic accidents,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker157
label: INTJc
text: even suicide rates.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker158
label: INTJc
text:
But as a deeper dive,
I want to focus on this:

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker159
label: INTJc
text: sleep loss and your immune system.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker160
label: INTJc
text:
And here, I'll introduce these delightful
blue elements in the image.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker161
label: INTJc
text: They are called natural killer cells,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker162
label: INTJc
text:
and you can think of natural killer cells
almost like the secret service agents

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker163
label: INTJc
text: of your immune system.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker164
label: INTJc
text:
They are very good at identifying
dangerous, unwanted elements

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker165
label: INTJc
text: and eliminating them.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker166
label: INTJc
text:
In fact, what they're doing here
is destroying a cancerous tumor mass.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker167
label: INTJc
text:
So what you wish for
is a virile set of these immune assassins

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker168
label: INTJc
text: at all times,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker169
label: INTJc
text:
and tragically, that's what you don't have
if you're not sleeping enough.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker170
label: INTJc
text: So here in this experiment,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker171
label: INTJc
text:
you're not going to have your sleep
deprived for an entire night,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker172
label: INTJc
text:
you're simply going to have your sleep
restricted to four hours

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker173
label: INTJc
text: for one single night,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker174
label: INTJc
text:
and then we're going to look to see
what's the percent reduction

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker175
label: INTJc
text: in immune cell activity that you suffer.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker176
label: INTJc
text: And it's not small -- it's not 10 percent,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker177
label: INTJc
text: it's not 20 percent.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker178
label: INTJc
text:
There was a 70-percent drop
in natural killer cell activity.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker179
label: INTJc
text:
That's a concerning state
of immune deficiency,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker180
label: INTJc
text:
and you can perhaps understand
why we're now finding

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker181
label: INTJc
text:
significant links between
short sleep duration

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker182
label: INTJc
text:
and your risk for the development
of numerous forms of cancer.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker183
label: INTJc
text:
Currently, that list includes
cancer of the bowel,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker184
label: INTJc
text:
cancer of the prostate
and cancer of the breast.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker185
label: INTJc
text:
In fact, the link between a lack of sleep
and cancer is now so strong

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker186
label: INTJc
text: that the World Health Organization

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker187
label: INTJc
text:
has classified any form
of nighttime shift work

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker188
label: INTJc
text: as a probable carcinogen,

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker189
label: INTJc
text:
because of a disruption
of your sleep-wake rhythms.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker190
label: INTJc
text: So you may have heard of that old maxim

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker191
label: INTJc
text: that you can sleep when you're dead.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker192
label: INTJc
text: Well, I'm being quite serious now --

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker193
label: INTJc
text: it is mortally unwise advice.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker194
label: INTJc
text:
We know this from epidemiological studies
across millions of individuals.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker195
label: INTJc
text: There's a simple truth:

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker196
label: INTJc
text:
the shorter your sleep,
the shorter your life.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker197
label: INTJc
text: Short sleep predicts all-cause mortality.

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker198
label: INTJc
text:
And if increasing your risk
for the development of cancer

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker199
label: INTJc
text: or even Alzheimer's disease

id: INTJc_Sleep is your superpower | Matt Walker200
label: INTJc
text: were not sufficiently disquieting,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy0
label: ESTJ
text:
Eight years ago, I was haunted
by an evil spirit.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy1
label: ESTJ
text: I was 25 at the time,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy2
label: ESTJ
text:
and I was living in a tiny house
behind someone else's house

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy3
label: ESTJ
text: in Los Angeles.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy4
label: ESTJ
text:
It was this guest house,
it had kind of been dilapidated,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy5
label: ESTJ
text: not taken care of for a long time.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy6
label: ESTJ
text: And one night, I was sitting there

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy7
label: ESTJ
text: and I got this really spooky feeling,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy8
label: ESTJ
text:
kind of the feeling
like you're being watched.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy9
label: ESTJ
text: But no one was there except my two dogs,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy10
label: ESTJ
text: and they were just chewing their feet.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy11
label: ESTJ
text: And I looked around. No one was there.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy12
label: ESTJ
text:
And I thought, OK,
it's just my imagination.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy13
label: ESTJ
text: But the feeling just kept getting worse,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy14
label: ESTJ
text:
and I started to feel
this pressure in my chest,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy15
label: ESTJ
text:
sort of like the feeling
when you get bad news.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy16
label: ESTJ
text: But it started to sink lower and lower

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy17
label: ESTJ
text: and almost hurt.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy18
label: ESTJ
text:
And over the course of that week,
this feeling got worse and worse,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy19
label: ESTJ
text:
and I started to become convinced
that something was there

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy20
label: ESTJ
text: in my little guest house, haunting me.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy21
label: ESTJ
text: And I started to hear these sounds,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy22
label: ESTJ
text:
this "whoosh," kind of whisper,
like something passing through me.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy23
label: ESTJ
text: I called my best friend, Claire, and said,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy24
label: ESTJ
text: "I know this is going to sound crazy,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy25
label: ESTJ
text: but, um ...

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy26
label: ESTJ
text:
I think there's a ghost in my house,
and I need to get rid of it."

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy27
label: ESTJ
text:
And she said -- she's very
open-minded -- and she said,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy28
label: ESTJ
text: "I don't think you're crazy.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy29
label: ESTJ
text:
I think you just need
to do a cleansing ritual."

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy30
label: ESTJ
text: (Laughter)

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy31
label: ESTJ
text: "So get some sage and burn it,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy32
label: ESTJ
text: and tell it to go away."

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy33
label: ESTJ
text:
So I said, "OK,"
and I went and I bought sage.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy34
label: ESTJ
text:
I had never done this before,
so I set the sage on fire,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy35
label: ESTJ
text:
waved it about, and said, "Go away!
This is my house! I live here.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy36
label: ESTJ
text: You don't live here!"

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy37
label: ESTJ
text:
But the feeling stayed.
Nothing got better.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy38
label: ESTJ
text: And then I started to think,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy39
label: ESTJ
text:
OK, well now this thing is probably
just laughing at me,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy40
label: ESTJ
text: because it hasn't left,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy41
label: ESTJ
text:
and I probably just look like
this impotent, powerless thing

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy42
label: ESTJ
text: that couldn't get it to go away.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy43
label: ESTJ
text: So every day I'd come home

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy44
label: ESTJ
text:
and you guys, this feeling got so bad
that -- I mean, I'm laughing at it now --

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy45
label: ESTJ
text:
but I would sit there in bed
and cry every night.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy46
label: ESTJ
text:
And the feeling on my chest
got worse and worse.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy47
label: ESTJ
text: It was physically painful.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy48
label: ESTJ
text: And I even went to a psychiatrist

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy49
label: ESTJ
text:
and tried to get her
to prescribe me medicine,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy50
label: ESTJ
text:
and she wouldn't just because
I don't have schizophrenia, OK.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy51
label: ESTJ
text: (Laughter)

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy52
label: ESTJ
text:
So finally I got on the internet,
and I Googled "hauntings."

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy53
label: ESTJ
text:
And I came upon this forum
of ghost hunters.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy54
label: ESTJ
text:
But these were a special
kind of ghost hunters --

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy55
label: ESTJ
text: they were skeptics.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy56
label: ESTJ
text:
They believed that every case of ghosts
that they had investigated so far

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy57
label: ESTJ
text: had been explained away by science.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy58
label: ESTJ
text:
And I was like, "OK, smart guys,
this is what's happening to me,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy59
label: ESTJ
text:
and if you have an explanation for me,
I would love to hear it."

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy60
label: ESTJ
text: And one of them said, "OK.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy61
label: ESTJ
text:
Um, have you heard
of carbon monoxide poisoning?"

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy62
label: ESTJ
text: And I said, "Yeah.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy63
label: ESTJ
text: Like, gas poisoning?"

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy64
label: ESTJ
text:
Carbon monoxide poisoning
is when you have a gas leak

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy65
label: ESTJ
text: leaking into your home.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy66
label: ESTJ
text:
I looked it up, and the symptoms
of carbon monoxide poisoning

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy67
label: ESTJ
text: include a pressure on your chest,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy68
label: ESTJ
text: auditory hallucinations -- whoosh --

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy69
label: ESTJ
text: and an unexplained feeling of dread.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy70
label: ESTJ
text: So that night, I called the gas company.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy71
label: ESTJ
text:
I said, "I have an emergency.
I need you to come out.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy72
label: ESTJ
text:
I don't want to get into the story now,
but I need you to come out."

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy73
label: ESTJ
text: (Laughter)

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy74
label: ESTJ
text:
They came out. I said,
"I suspect a gas leak."

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy75
label: ESTJ
text:
They brought their carbon
monoxide detector,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy76
label: ESTJ
text: and the man said,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy77
label: ESTJ
text:
"It's a really good thing
that you called us tonight,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy78
label: ESTJ
text:
because you could have been
dead very soon."

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy79
label: ESTJ
text:
Thirty-seven percent of Americans
believe in haunted houses,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy80
label: ESTJ
text:
and I wonder how many of them
have been in one

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy81
label: ESTJ
text: and how many of them have been in danger.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy82
label: ESTJ
text:
So that haunting story
has led me to my job.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy83
label: ESTJ
text:
I'm an investigator, and I'm
an investigator in two senses:

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy84
label: ESTJ
text: I'm an investigative journalist,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy85
label: ESTJ
text:
and I'm also an investigator
of the claims of the paranormal

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy86
label: ESTJ
text: and claims of the spiritual.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy87
label: ESTJ
text: And that means a few things.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy88
label: ESTJ
text:
Sometimes that means that I'm pretending
to need an exorcism

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy89
label: ESTJ
text:
so I can get -- yes, that's right! --
so I can go to an exorcist

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy90
label: ESTJ
text:
and see if he's using gimmicks
or psychological tricks

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy91
label: ESTJ
text:
to try to convince someone
that they're possessed.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy92
label: ESTJ
text:
Sometimes that means
I'm going undercover in a fringe group

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy93
label: ESTJ
text:
which I report on
for a podcast that I co-host.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy94
label: ESTJ
text:
And I've done over 70 investigations
like this with my co-host, Ross.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy95
label: ESTJ
text:
I would love to tell you
that nine times out of 10, science wins,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy96
label: ESTJ
text: saves the day, it's all explained.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy97
label: ESTJ
text: That's not true.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy98
label: ESTJ
text:
The truth is, 10 times out of 10,
science wins, it saves the day.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy99
label: ESTJ
text: (Applause)

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy100
label: ESTJ
text:
And that doesn't mean
there's no such thing as a mystery.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy101
label: ESTJ
text:
Of course there are mysteries,
but a mystery is a mystery.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy102
label: ESTJ
text: It is not a ghost.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy103
label: ESTJ
text:
Now, I believe there are
two kinds of truth,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy104
label: ESTJ
text:
and it's taken me a while to get
to this place, but I think this is right,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy105
label: ESTJ
text: so hear me out.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy106
label: ESTJ
text:
I think there is outer truth
and there's inner truth.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy107
label: ESTJ
text: So if you say to me,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy108
label: ESTJ
text:
"There was a man named Jesus
and he once existed,"

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy109
label: ESTJ
text: that's outer truth, right?

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy110
label: ESTJ
text:
And we can go and look
at the historical record.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy111
label: ESTJ
text:
We can determine
whether that seems to be true.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy112
label: ESTJ
text:
And I would argue,
it does seem to be true.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy113
label: ESTJ
text:
If you say, "Jesus rose
from the dead," -- ooh, trickier.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy114
label: ESTJ
text: (Laughter)

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy115
label: ESTJ
text: I would say that's an outer-truth claim,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy116
label: ESTJ
text: because he physically rose or he didn't.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy117
label: ESTJ
text:
I'm not going to get into
whether he rose or he didn't,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy118
label: ESTJ
text:
but I would say
that's an outer-truth claim.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy119
label: ESTJ
text: It happened or it didn't happen.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy120
label: ESTJ
text:
But if you say, "I don't care
whether he rose from the dead.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy121
label: ESTJ
text: It's symbolically important to me,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy122
label: ESTJ
text:
and that metaphor is so meaningful,
so purposeful to me,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy123
label: ESTJ
text:
and I'm not going to try
to persuade you of it,"

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy124
label: ESTJ
text:
now you've moved it
from outer truth to inner truth,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy125
label: ESTJ
text: from science to art.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy126
label: ESTJ
text:
And I think we have a tendency
to not be clear about this,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy127
label: ESTJ
text:
to try to move our inner truths
to outer truths,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy128
label: ESTJ
text: or to not be fair about it to each other,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy129
label: ESTJ
text:
and when people are telling us
their inner truths,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy130
label: ESTJ
text:
to try to make them defend them
by outer-truth standards.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy131
label: ESTJ
text:
So I'm talking here about outer truth,
about objective things.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy132
label: ESTJ
text:
And there was an objective reality
in my haunted house, right?

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy133
label: ESTJ
text: Now that I've told you about the gas leak,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy134
label: ESTJ
text:
I doubt a single person here
would be like,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy135
label: ESTJ
text: "I still think there was a ghost, too" --

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy136
label: ESTJ
text: (Laughter)

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy137
label: ESTJ
text:
because as soon as we have
these scientific explanations,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy138
label: ESTJ
text: we know to give up the ghost.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy139
label: ESTJ
text:
We use these things as stopgaps
for things that we can't explain.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy140
label: ESTJ
text: We don't believe them because of evidence;

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy141
label: ESTJ
text:
we believe them because
of a lack of evidence.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy142
label: ESTJ
text: So there is a group in Los Angeles

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy143
label: ESTJ
text:
called the Independent
Investigations Group, or the IIG,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy144
label: ESTJ
text: and they do great work.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy145
label: ESTJ
text: They'll give a $10,000 prize

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy146
label: ESTJ
text:
to anyone who can show,
under scientific conditions,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy147
label: ESTJ
text: that they have a paranormal ability.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy148
label: ESTJ
text: No one's done it yet,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy149
label: ESTJ
text:
but they've had a couple people
who claim that they were clairaudients,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy150
label: ESTJ
text:
which means that they can hear voices
either from the great beyond

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy151
label: ESTJ
text: or they can read minds.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy152
label: ESTJ
text:
And they had one person
who was very sincere,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy153
label: ESTJ
text: who believed that he could read minds.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy154
label: ESTJ
text:
So they set up a test with him,
and this is the way it always works.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy155
label: ESTJ
text: The group says, "OK, we have a protocol,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy156
label: ESTJ
text: we have a way to scientifically test this.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy157
label: ESTJ
text: Do you agree with it?"

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy158
label: ESTJ
text: The person says yes. Then they test it.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy159
label: ESTJ
text: It's very important that both sides agree.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy160
label: ESTJ
text: They did that, they tested him.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy161
label: ESTJ
text: They said, "OK, you know what?

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy162
label: ESTJ
text:
You weren't able to predict
what Lisa was thinking.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy163
label: ESTJ
text: It matched up about the same as chance.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy164
label: ESTJ
text: Looks like you don't have the power."

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy165
label: ESTJ
text: And that gave them the opportunity

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy166
label: ESTJ
text:
to compassionately sit down with him
and have a very difficult discussion,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy167
label: ESTJ
text: which basically amounted to,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy168
label: ESTJ
text:
"Hey, we know you're sincere,
and what that means is,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy169
label: ESTJ
text: you do hear something in your head."

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy170
label: ESTJ
text:
And that guy got to make
the very difficult decision,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy171
label: ESTJ
text:
but really the life-changing decision
about whether to go get help.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy172
label: ESTJ
text:
We're actually helping people
to make these connections

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy173
label: ESTJ
text:
that maybe before seemed like
otherworldly explanations,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy174
label: ESTJ
text:
help draw us into reality
and maybe change our lives for the better.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy175
label: ESTJ
text:
Now, on the other hand,
maybe one time it'll turn out to be true.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy176
label: ESTJ
text: Maybe we'll find out there are ghosts,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy177
label: ESTJ
text: and holy shit, it will be the best thing!

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy178
label: ESTJ
text:
And every time I do
one of these investigations,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy179
label: ESTJ
text: I still get so excited,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy180
label: ESTJ
text: and I'm like 75 into them,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy181
label: ESTJ
text:
and still I swear on number 76,
I'm going to be like, "This is the one!"

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy182
label: ESTJ
text: (Laughter)

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy183
label: ESTJ
text:
Maybe I'm just eternally optimistic,
but I hope I never lose this hope,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy184
label: ESTJ
text:
and I invite you to take
this same attitude

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy185
label: ESTJ
text:
when people share
their outer beliefs with you.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy186
label: ESTJ
text: When talking about testable claims,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy187
label: ESTJ
text:
respect them enough to ask
these good questions.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy188
label: ESTJ
text:
Challenge and see
how you can examine them together,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy189
label: ESTJ
text:
because there's this idea
that you can't respect a belief

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy190
label: ESTJ
text:
and still challenge it,
but that's not true.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy191
label: ESTJ
text:
When we jiggle the lock,
when we test the claim,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy192
label: ESTJ
text:
we're saying, OK, I respect you,
I'm listening to what you're saying,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy193
label: ESTJ
text: I'm going to test it out with you.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy194
label: ESTJ
text:
We've all had that experience
where you're telling someone something,

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy195
label: ESTJ
text:
and they're like, "Oh,
that's really interesting, yeah,"

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy196
label: ESTJ
text: you know you're being had.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy197
label: ESTJ
text: But when someone says, "Really? Huh.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy198
label: ESTJ
text:
Sounds a little sketchy to me,
but I'm listening,"

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy199
label: ESTJ
text:
you at least know
you're being engaged and respected.

id: ESTJ_A scientific approach to the paranormal | Carrie Poppy200
label: ESTJ
text:
And that's the kind of attitude
we should have with these claims.
